article.description: Prentiss Nixon and J.D. Paige scored 18 points apiece as Colorado State held on to edge San Jose State 76-71 in a Mountain West matchup on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Colorado State edges San Jose State 76-71
article.linkText: Colorado State edges San Jose State 76-71
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. -- Prentiss Nixon and J.D. Paige scored 18 points apiece as Colorado State held on to edge San Jose State 76-71 in a Mountain West matchup on Wednesday night. Gian Clavell added 15 points for the Rams (10-6, 2-1) and Emmanuel Omogbo had 13 points and 11 rebounds for his seventh double-double this season. Paige and Omogbo teamed up for seven unanswered points early in the second period to help extend the Rams' three-point intermission lead to 53-46 with 11:55 to play. San Jose State closed it to 72-71 with 1:43 remaining, but Paige sank a jumper and the Spartans' Ryan Welage missed a 3-pointer with seven seconds left to seal it. Colorado State jumped to a 13-0 start and was up 34-31 at the break. Brandon Clarke scored 24 points and grabbed nine rebounds for the Spartans (7-6, 0-2). E.J. Boyce added 12 points off the bench.
